posts.title: Why Trump's debate wasn't bad for him and was bad for Kamala
posts.content:
Very long, so I understand if you don't want to read it, but here it is and I'll have a tl;dr summary at the end.

A lot has been said about how Biden's performance was so bad at his debate that Kamala comes away looking like a master orator in comparison.

Well the other side is true too. Because Trump executed a flawless victory last time, because his opponent last time gave zero resistance, his performance last night looks worse than it was because of the comparison to the last debate.

Not only was he challenged with constant lies, competent though meaningless jargon from Kamala compared to Biden's incompetent trailings off, he was also introduced to new lies that he wasn't prepared for. Usually they go after the same old things that he's prepared for. The whole "people leave your audiences early" got under his skin and made him stumble a bit because as far as I know, it's a new lie, one he probably hasn't prepared for, so he just starts responding because of it's outrageou-ness.

But regardless of all this context, in a vacuum not factoring in the past debate which was legendarily bad for the democrats, Trump doesn't look as bad as it's been made out and Kamala doesn't look as good as it's made out.

Trump always has good parts where he nails it in every debate, and he always has fumbles and missed opportunities. The debate with Joe Biden was the lone exception because he had zero opposition in that debate. So really Trump's performance was more or less in line with all his other performances. There were parts where we go "I wish he would have driven this point more, or not gotten sidetracked by this point" and then there's parts where he was very effective and gets some good one liner sound bites in like "see spot run".

But the major take away is this:

Kamala could not respond to anything Trump said....literally not one point. The best she could do was make faces, even as he's accusing her dad of being a Marxist professor. Not one point of policy could she rebut.

You see, as much as we would have LIKED a better performance from Trump last night, what the democrats NEEDED from Kamala was an excellent performance. And she did not give an excellent performance. She started off the debate responding to the question "are we better off than 4 years" with some story about being raised middle class.

She didn't give 1 straight answer to 1 straight question. Meanwhile Trump may have had a few fumbles, but he answered decisively and as often as possible highlighted Kamala's weakness.

All the conversation is around how Trump did, but almost no one is talking about how Kamala did, and objectively how did Kamala do? Awful. Again, beating this point again, but she did not answer a single question and couldn't rebut Trump's accurate blaming of her and her disastrous border and economy as Vice President.

Again, let's not forget that Kamala is the least popular presidential candidate in history as she was always the first to drop out in the primaries which Trump pointed out and she had no response to. Considering that, what they needed from Kamala was a slam dunk of a debate.

Was this Trump's best debate. Well considering it was a 3 on 1 with the most unfair rules imaginable, he didn't do horribly, but no, it wasn't Trump's best debate.

Was this debate the level of quality that Kamala needed to achieve to make any sway with independents? No. Name one thing that Kamala said that will resonate with independent normies who are getting disenfranchised with high prices and unchecked illegal immigration. She needed to resonate with the independents and she couldn't bring it. Look at how panicked she was whenever Trump brought up how she's against fracking which she's been on video vocally being against. That shows you what she and the dems knew was at stake....and I argue she did nothing to earn the normie blue collar independent vote in Pennslyvania.

Look her slogan, the thing that they tried to get to be her platform is "let's turn the page" which she kept repeating, whatever the heck that means.

To a normie independent looking at their grocery bill and the illegal immigrant crime, will the phrase "let's turn the page" or "Make America Great Again" resonate more in their mind?

So the tl;dr version

Kamala being the most unpopular candidate was the one who had to deliver a knockout performance. Trump made a few mistakes (understandable considering the environment), but was in line with most of his debate performances. Kamala did not deliver a knockout performance. All analysis has been done on how Trump did, and almost none has been done on how Kamala did. She didn't answer a single question, and had no good responses to Trump's highlighting of her radical unpopular policies and values. We always want Trump to do the best in a debate, but in this specific debate the democrats NEEDED Kamala to convince Independents and her performance did not do that, which is an understatement.
